segment.source: Data Sent Through the Microsoft Compatibility Exchange (Windows 10)
segment.target: Data Sent Through the Microsoft Compatibility Exchange (Windows 10)

segment.source: The Microsoft Compatibility Exchange propagates data of various types between Microsoft Corporation, independent software vendors (ISVs) and the Application Compatibility Toolkit (ACT) Community.
segment.target: The Microsoft Compatibility Exchange propagates data of various types between Microsoft Corporation, independent software vendors (ISVs) and the Application Compatibility Toolkit (ACT) Community.

segment.source: Data Sent Through the Microsoft Compatibility Exchange
segment.target: Data Sent Through the Microsoft Compatibility Exchange

segment.source: The Microsoft Compatibility Exchange propagates data of various types between Microsoft Corporation, independent software vendors (ISVs) and the Application Compatibility Toolkit (ACT) Community.
segment.target: The Microsoft Compatibility Exchange propagates data of various types between Microsoft Corporation, independent software vendors (ISVs) and the Application Compatibility Toolkit (ACT) Community.

segment.source: During synchronization, the Microsoft Compatibility Exchange sends the following information to Microsoft Corporation:
segment.target: During synchronization, the Microsoft Compatibility Exchange sends the following information to Microsoft Corporation:

segment.source: This data includes the application name, the vendor, the version number, the language, and the deployment type.
segment.target: This data includes the application name, the vendor, the version number, the language, and the deployment type.

segment.source: The data-synchronization process does not send your list of URLs visited as part of the information exchange.
segment.target: The data-synchronization process does not send your list of URLs visited as part of the information exchange.

segment.source: Data Sent to the ACT Community
segment.target: Data Sent to the ACT Community

segment.source: The Microsoft Compatibility Exchange sends the following information to the ACT Community for each application that you decide to share with the ACT Community:
segment.target: The Microsoft Compatibility Exchange sends the following information to the ACT Community for each application that you decide to share with the ACT Community:

segment.source: This data includes the application name, the vendor, the version number, the language, and the deployment type.
segment.target: This data includes the application name, the vendor, the version number, the language, and the deployment type.

segment.source: The database GUID that identifies the organization that is the source of the data.
segment.target: The database GUID that identifies the organization that is the source of the data.

segment.source: The platform and destination operating system.
segment.target: The platform and destination operating system.

segment.source: The issue and solution published date.
segment.target: The issue and solution published date.

segment.source: The data-synchronization process does not send your list of URLs visited as part of the information exchange.
segment.target: The data-synchronization process does not send your list of URLs visited as part of the information exchange.

segment.source: After you send your data, the Microsoft Compatibility Exchange matches your application properties against the known issues listed in the Application Profile database.
segment.target: After you send your data, the Microsoft Compatibility Exchange matches your application properties against the known issues listed in the Application Profile database.

segment.source: The Microsoft Compatibility Exchange downloads any issues and corresponding solutions that match your application set and then stores the information in your ACT database.
segment.target: The Microsoft Compatibility Exchange downloads any issues and corresponding solutions that match your application set and then stores the information in your ACT database.

segment.source: Data Sent From Microsoft and ISVs
segment.target: Data Sent From Microsoft and ISVs

segment.source: For each application that matches an application in the Application Profile database, the Microsoft Compatibility Exchange returns the following information, provided by authoritative sources including Microsoft Corporation and independent software vendors (ISVs).
segment.target: For each application that matches an application in the Application Profile database, the Microsoft Compatibility Exchange returns the following information, provided by authoritative sources including Microsoft Corporation and independent software vendors (ISVs).

segment.source: The determination of whether the application has compatibility issues.
segment.target: The determination of whether the application has compatibility issues.

segment.source: A unique ID number for the compatibility issue.
segment.target: A unique ID number for the compatibility issue.

segment.source: Impact this issue has on the application experience.
segment.target: Impact this issue has on the application experience.

segment.source: Degree of impact that this issue has on your organization.
segment.target: Degree of impact that this issue has on your organization.

segment.source: Date that the source entered the data into the database.
segment.target: Date that the source entered the data into the database.

segment.source: Friendly name of the installed operating system.
segment.target: Friendly name of the installed operating system.

segment.source: Major version number of the operating system.
segment.target: Major version number of the operating system.

segment.source: Minor version number of the operating system.
segment.target: Minor version number of the operating system.

segment.source: Language ID of the application to which the compatibility issue applies.
segment.target: Language ID of the application to which the compatibility issue applies.

segment.source: Short title of the compatibility issue.
segment.target: Short title of the compatibility issue.

segment.source: Major version number of the operating system service pack.
segment.target: Major version number of the operating system service pack.

segment.source: Minor version number of the operating system service pack.
segment.target: Minor version number of the operating system service pack.

segment.source: URL of any links provided for the compatibility issue.
segment.target: URL of any links provided for the compatibility issue.

segment.source: IDs for the source of the compatibility issue's solution.
segment.target: IDs for the source of the compatibility issue's solution.

segment.source: Type of solution provided for the compatibility issue.
segment.target: Type of solution provided for the compatibility issue.

segment.source: Language ID of the application to which the solution applies.
segment.target: Language ID of the application to which the solution applies.

segment.source: URL of any links provided for the compatibility issue solution.
segment.target: URL of any links provided for the compatibility issue solution.

segment.target: Data Sent From the ACT Community

segment.source: For each application that matches an application in the Application Profile database, the Microsoft Compatibility Exchange returns the following ACT Community information, which you receive only if you are a member of the ACT Community:
segment.target: For each application that matches an application in the Application Profile database, the Microsoft Compatibility Exchange returns the following ACT Community information, which you receive only if you are a member of the ACT Community:

segment.source: The count of Works ratings, for 32-bit and 64-bit operating systems.
segment.target: The count of Works ratings, for 32-bit and 64-bit operating systems.

segment.source: Works with Minor Issues or has Solutions
segment.target: Works with Minor Issues or has Solutions

segment.source: The count of Works with Minor Issues or has Solutions ratings, for 32-bit and 64-bit operating systems.
segment.target: The count of Works with Minor Issues or has Solutions ratings, for 32-bit and 64-bit operating systems.

segment.source: The count of Does Not Work ratings, for 32-bit and 64-bit operating systems.
segment.target: The count of Does Not Work ratings, for 32-bit and 64-bit operating systems.
